{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This strange-looking plant is called the Llareta."},{"time":4000,"text":"What looks like moss covering rocks"},{"time":6000,"text":"is actually a shrub"},{"time":8000,"text":"comprised of thousands of branches,"},{"time":10000,"text":"each containing clusters of tiny green leaves at the end"},{"time":13000,"text":"and so densely packed together"},{"time":15000,"text":"that you could actually stand on top of it."},{"time":18000,"text":"This individual lives in the Atacama Desert in Chile,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and it happens to be 3,000 years old."},{"time":24000,"text":"It also happens to be a relative of parsley."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"For the past five years, I've been researching,"},{"time":29000,"text":"working with biologists"},{"time":31000,"text":"and traveling all over the world"},{"time":33000,"text":"to find continuously living organisms"},{"time":35000,"text":"that are 2,000 years old and older."},{"time":38000,"text":"The project is part art and part science."},{"time":40000,"text":"There's an environmental component."},{"time":42000,"text":"And I'm also trying to create a means"},{"time":44000,"text":"in which to step outside our quotidian experience of time"},{"time":47000,"text":"and to start to consider a deeper timescale."},{"time":50000,"text":"I selected 2,000 years as my minimum age"},{"time":53000,"text":"because I wanted to start at what we consider to be year zero"},{"time":56000,"text":"and work backward from there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"What you're looking at now is a tree called Jomon Sugi,"},{"time":61000,"text":"living on the remote island of Yakushima."},{"time":64000,"text":"The tree was in part a catalyst for the project."},{"time":67000,"text":"I'd been traveling in Japan"},{"time":69000,"text":"without an agenda other than to photograph,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and then I heard about this tree"},{"time":73000,"text":"that is 2,180 years old"},{"time":76000,"text":"and knew that I had to go visit it."},{"time":79000,"text":"It wasn't until later, when I was actually back home in New York"},{"time":82000,"text":"that I got the idea for the project."},{"time":84000,"text":"So it was the slow churn, if you will."},{"time":86000,"text":"I think it was my longstanding desire"},{"time":88000,"text":"to bring together my interest"},{"time":90000,"text":"in art, science and philosophy"},{"time":92000,"text":"that allowed me to be ready"},{"time":94000,"text":"when the proverbial light bulb went on."},{"time":96000,"text":"So I started researching, and to my surprise,"},{"time":98000,"text":"this project had never been done before"},{"time":100000,"text":"in the arts or the sciences."},{"time":102000,"text":"And -- perhaps naively --"},{"time":104000,"text":"I was surprised to find that there isn't even an area in the sciences"},{"time":107000,"text":"that deals with this idea"},{"time":109000,"text":"of global species longevity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"So what you're looking at here"},{"time":113000,"text":"is the rhizocarpon geographicum, or map lichen,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and this is around 3,000 years old"},{"time":118000,"text":"and lives in Greenland,"},{"time":120000,"text":"which is a long way to go for some lichens."},{"time":123000,"text":"Visiting Greenland was more like"},{"time":125000,"text":"traveling back in time"},{"time":127000,"text":"than just traveling very far north."},{"time":129000,"text":"It was very primal and more remote"},{"time":131000,"text":"than anything I'd ever experienced before."},{"time":134000,"text":"And this is heightened by a couple of particular experiences."},{"time":137000,"text":"One was when I had been dropped off by boat"},{"time":140000,"text":"on a remote fjord,"},{"time":142000,"text":"only to find that the archeologists I was supposed to meet"},{"time":144000,"text":"were nowhere to be found."},{"time":146000,"text":"And it's not like you could send them a text or shoot them an e-mail,"},{"time":149000,"text":"so I was literally left to my own devices."},{"time":152000,"text":"But luckily, it worked out obviously,"},{"time":155000,"text":"but it was a humbling experience"},{"time":157000,"text":"to feel so disconnected."},{"time":160000,"text":"And then a few days later,"},{"time":162000,"text":"we had the opportunity to go fishing in a glacial stream"},{"time":164000,"text":"near our campsite,"},{"time":166000,"text":"where the fish were so abundant"},{"time":169000,"text":"that you could literally reach into the stream"},{"time":172000,"text":"and grab out a foot-long trout with your bare hands."},{"time":175000,"text":"It was like visiting"},{"time":177000,"text":"a more innocent time on the planet."},{"time":180000,"text":"And then, of course, there's the lichens."},{"time":182000,"text":"These lichens grow only one centimeter"},{"time":184000,"text":"every hundred years."},{"time":186000,"text":"I think that really puts human lifespans"},{"time":188000,"text":"into a different perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"And what you're looking at here"},{"time":192000,"text":"is an aerial photo take over eastern Oregon."},{"time":194000,"text":"And if the title \"Searching for Armillaria Death Rings,\""},{"time":197000,"text":"sounds ominous, it is."},{"time":200000,"text":"The Armillaria is actually a predatory fungus,"},{"time":203000,"text":"killing certain species of trees in the forest."},{"time":206000,"text":"It's also more benignly known"},{"time":208000,"text":"as the honey mushroom or the \"humongous fungus\""},{"time":211000,"text":"because it happens to be"},{"time":213000,"text":"one of the world's largest organisms as well."},{"time":215000,"text":"So with the help of some biologists studying the fungus,"},{"time":218000,"text":"I got some maps and some GPS coordinates"},{"time":221000,"text":"and chartered a plane"},{"time":223000,"text":"and started looking for the death rings,"},{"time":226000,"text":"the circular patterns"},{"time":228000,"text":"in which the fungus kills the trees."},{"time":230000,"text":"So I'm not sure if there are any in this photo,"},{"time":232000,"text":"but I do know the fungus is down there."},{"time":234000,"text":"And then this back down on the ground"},{"time":236000,"text":"and you can see that the fungus is actually invading this tree."},{"time":239000,"text":"So that white material that you see"},{"time":241000,"text":"in between the bark and the wood"},{"time":243000,"text":"is the mycelial felt of the fungus,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and what it's doing -- it's actually"},{"time":248000,"text":"slowly strangling the tree to death"},{"time":250000,"text":"by preventing the flow of water and nutrients."},{"time":253000,"text":"So this strategy has served it pretty well --"},{"time":255000,"text":"it's 2,400 years old."},{"time":258000,"text":"And then from underground to underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"This is a Brain Coral living in Tobago"},{"time":263000,"text":"that's around 2,000 years old."},{"time":265000,"text":"And I had to overcome my fear of deep water to find this one."},{"time":268000,"text":"This is at about 60 feet"},{"time":270000,"text":"or 18 meters, depth."},{"time":272000,"text":"And you'll see, there's some damage to the surface of the coral."},{"time":275000,"text":"That was actually caused by a school of parrot fish"},{"time":278000,"text":"that had started eating it,"},{"time":280000,"text":"though luckily, they lost interest before killing it."},{"time":283000,"text":"Luckily still, it seems to be out of harm's way"},{"time":286000,"text":"of the recent oil spill."},{"time":288000,"text":"But that being said, we just as easily could have lost"},{"time":290000,"text":"one of the oldest living things on the planet,"},{"time":293000,"text":"and the full impact of that disaster"},{"time":295000,"text":"is still yet to be seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"Now this is something that I think"},{"time":299000,"text":"is one of the most quietly resilient things on the planet."},{"time":302000,"text":"This is clonal colony"},{"time":304000,"text":"of Quaking Aspen trees, living in Utah,"},{"time":307000,"text":"that is literally 80,000 years old."},{"time":310000,"text":"What looks like a forest"},{"time":312000,"text":"is actually only one tree."},{"time":315000,"text":"Imagine that it's one giant root system"},{"time":317000,"text":"and each tree is a stem"},{"time":319000,"text":"coming up from that system."},{"time":321000,"text":"So what you have is one giant,"},{"time":323000,"text":"interconnected,"},{"time":325000,"text":"genetically identical individual"},{"time":327000,"text":"that's been living for 80,000 years."},{"time":330000,"text":"It also happens to be male"},{"time":332000,"text":"and, in theory immortal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"This is a clonal tree as well."},{"time":339000,"text":"This is the spruce Gran Picea,"},{"time":341000,"text":"which at 9,550 years"},{"time":343000,"text":"is a mere babe in the woods."},{"time":345000,"text":"The location of this tree"},{"time":347000,"text":"is actually kept secret for its own protection."},{"time":350000,"text":"I spoke to the biologist who discovered this tree,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and he told me that that spindly growth you see there in the center"},{"time":356000,"text":"is most likely a product of climate change."},{"time":359000,"text":"As it's gotten warmer on the top of the mountain,"},{"time":362000,"text":"the vegetation zone is actually changing."},{"time":365000,"text":"So we don't even necessarily have to have"},{"time":367000,"text":"direct contact with these organisms"},{"time":369000,"text":"to have a very real impact on them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"This is the Fortingall Yew --"},{"time":376000,"text":"no, I'm just kidding --"},{"time":378000,"text":"this is the Fortingall Yew."},{"time":380000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":382000,"text":"But I put that slide in there"},{"time":384000,"text":"because I'm often asked if there are any animals in the project."},{"time":387000,"text":"And aside from coral,"},{"time":389000,"text":"the answer is no."},{"time":391000,"text":"Does anybody know how old the oldest tortoise is --"},{"time":394000,"text":"any guesses?"},{"time":396000,"text":"(Audience: 300.)"},{"time":398000,"text":"Rachel Sussman: 300? No, 175"},{"time":400000,"text":"is the oldest living tortoise,"},{"time":402000,"text":"so nowhere near 2,000."},{"time":405000,"text":"And then, you might have heard"},{"time":407000,"text":"of this giant clam that was discovered"},{"time":409000,"text":"off the coast of northern Iceland"},{"time":411000,"text":"that reached 405 years old."},{"time":414000,"text":"However, it died in the lab"},{"time":416000,"text":"as they were determining its age."},{"time":419000,"text":"The most interesting discovery of late, I think"},{"time":421000,"text":"is the so-called immortal jellyfish,"},{"time":424000,"text":"which has actually been observed in the lab"},{"time":426000,"text":"to be able to be able to revert back to the polyp state"},{"time":429000,"text":"after reaching full maturity."},{"time":431000,"text":"So that being said,"},{"time":434000,"text":"it's highly unlikely that any jellyfish would survive that long in the wild."},{"time":438000,"text":"And back to the yew here."},{"time":440000,"text":"So as you can see, it's in a churchyard;"},{"time":442000,"text":"it's in Scotland. It's behind a protective wall."},{"time":445000,"text":"And there are actually a number or ancient yews"},{"time":447000,"text":"in churchyards around the U.K.,"},{"time":449000,"text":"but if you do the math, you'll remember"},{"time":451000,"text":"it's actually the yew trees that were there first, then the churches."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"And now down to another part of the world."},{"time":458000,"text":"I had the opportunity to travel around the Limpopo Province in South Africa"},{"time":461000,"text":"with an expert in Baobab trees."},{"time":463000,"text":"And we saw a number of them,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and this is most likely the oldest."},{"time":467000,"text":"It's around 2,000,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and it's called the Sagole Baobab."},{"time":471000,"text":"And you know, I think of all of these organisms"},{"time":473000,"text":"as palimpsests."},{"time":475000,"text":"They contain thousands of years"},{"time":477000,"text":"of their own histories within themselves,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and they also contain records of natural and human events."},{"time":482000,"text":"And the Baobabs in particular"},{"time":484000,"text":"are a great example of this."},{"time":486000,"text":"You can see that this one"},{"time":488000,"text":"has names carved into its trunk,"},{"time":490000,"text":"but it also records some natural events."},{"time":492000,"text":"So the Baobabs, as they get older,"},{"time":494000,"text":"tend to get pulpy in their centers and hollow out."},{"time":497000,"text":"And this can create"},{"time":499000,"text":"great natural shelters for animals,"},{"time":501000,"text":"but they've also been appropriated"},{"time":503000,"text":"for some rather dubious human uses,"},{"time":505000,"text":"including a bar, a prison"},{"time":508000,"text":"and even a toilet inside of a tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"And this brings me to another favorite of mine --"},{"time":513000,"text":"I think, because it is just so unusual."},{"time":516000,"text":"This plant is called the Welwitschia,"},{"time":518000,"text":"and it lives only in parts of coastal Namibia and Angola,"},{"time":521000,"text":"where it's uniquely adapted"},{"time":523000,"text":"to collect moisture from mist coming off the sea."},{"time":526000,"text":"And what's more, it's actually a tree."},{"time":529000,"text":"It's a primitive conifer."},{"time":531000,"text":"You'll notice that it's bearing cones down the center."},{"time":534000,"text":"And what looks like two big heaps of leaves,"},{"time":537000,"text":"is actually two single leaves"},{"time":539000,"text":"that get shredded up"},{"time":541000,"text":"by the harsh desert conditions over time."},{"time":543000,"text":"And it actually never sheds those leaves,"},{"time":546000,"text":"so it also bears the distinction"},{"time":548000,"text":"of having the longest leaves"},{"time":550000,"text":"in the plant kingdom."},{"time":552000,"text":"I spoke to a biologist"},{"time":554000,"text":"at the Kirstenbosch Botanical Garden in Capetown"},{"time":556000,"text":"to ask him"},{"time":558000,"text":"where he thought this remarkable plant came from,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and his thought was that"},{"time":563000,"text":"if you travel around Namibia,"},{"time":565000,"text":"you see that there are a number of petrified forests,"},{"time":567000,"text":"and the logs are all --"},{"time":570000,"text":"the logs are all giant coniferous trees,"},{"time":573000,"text":"and yet there's no sign of where they might have come from."},{"time":576000,"text":"So his thought was that"},{"time":578000,"text":"flooding in the north of Africa"},{"time":580000,"text":"actually brought those coniferous trees down"},{"time":583000,"text":"tens of thousands of years ago,"},{"time":585000,"text":"and what resulted was this remarkable adaptation"},{"time":588000,"text":"to this unique desert environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"This is what I think is the most poetic of the oldest living things."},{"time":593000,"text":"This is something called an underground forest."},{"time":596000,"text":"So, I spoke to a botanist at the Pretoria Botanical Garden,"},{"time":599000,"text":"who explained that certain species of trees"},{"time":602000,"text":"have adapted to this region."},{"time":605000,"text":"It's bushfelt region,"},{"time":607000,"text":"which is dry and prone to a lot of fires,"},{"time":609000,"text":"as so what these trees have done"},{"time":612000,"text":"is, if you can imagine that this is the crown of the tree,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and that this is ground level,"},{"time":616000,"text":"imagine that the whole thing,"},{"time":618000,"text":"that whole bulk of the tree,"},{"time":620000,"text":"migrated underground,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and you just have those leaves peeping up above the surface."},{"time":625000,"text":"That way, when a fire roars through,"},{"time":627000,"text":"it's the equivalent of getting your eyebrows singed."},{"time":630000,"text":"The tree can easily recover."},{"time":633000,"text":"These also tend to grow clonally,"},{"time":635000,"text":"the oldest of which is 13,000 years old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"Back in the U.S., there's a couple plants of similar age."},{"time":641000,"text":"This is the clonal Creosote bush,"},{"time":643000,"text":"which is around 12,000 years old."},{"time":645000,"text":"If you've been in the American West,"},{"time":647000,"text":"you know the Creosote bush is pretty ubiquitous,"},{"time":649000,"text":"but that being said, you see that this has"},{"time":651000,"text":"this unique, circular form."},{"time":653000,"text":"And what's happening is it's expanding slowly outwards"},{"time":656000,"text":"from that original shape."},{"time":659000,"text":"And it's one -- again, that interconnected root system,"},{"time":662000,"text":"making it one genetically identical individual."},{"time":665000,"text":"It also has a friend nearby --"},{"time":668000,"text":"well, I think they're friends."},{"time":670000,"text":"This is the clonal Mojave yucca, it's about a mile away,"},{"time":673000,"text":"and it's a little bit older than 12,000 years."},{"time":675000,"text":"And you see it has that similar circular form."},{"time":678000,"text":"And there's some younger clones"},{"time":680000,"text":"dotting the landscape behind it."},{"time":682000,"text":"And both of these, the yucca and the Creosote bush,"},{"time":685000,"text":"live on Bureau of Land Management land,"},{"time":688000,"text":"and that's very different from being protected in a national park."},{"time":691000,"text":"In fact, this land is designated"},{"time":693000,"text":"for recreational all-terrain vehicle use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"So, now I want to show what very well might be"},{"time":702000,"text":"the oldest living thing on the planet."},{"time":704000,"text":"This is Siberian Actinobacteria,"},{"time":706000,"text":"which is between 400,000"},{"time":709000,"text":"and 600,000 years old."},{"time":712000,"text":"This bacteria was discovered several years ago"},{"time":714000,"text":"by a team of planetary biologists"},{"time":716000,"text":"hoping to find clues to life on other planets"},{"time":719000,"text":"by looking at one of the harshest conditions on ours."},{"time":722000,"text":"And what they found, by doing research into the permafrost,"},{"time":725000,"text":"was this bacteria."},{"time":727000,"text":"But what's unique about it is that"},{"time":729000,"text":"it's doing DNA repair below freezing."},{"time":731000,"text":"And what that means is that it's not dormant --"},{"time":734000,"text":"it's actually been living and growing"},{"time":736000,"text":"for half a million years."},{"time":739000,"text":"It's also probably one the most vulnerable"},{"time":742000,"text":"of the oldest living things,"},{"time":744000,"text":"because if the permafrost melts,"},{"time":746000,"text":"it won't survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"This is a map that I've put together of the oldest living things,"},{"time":750000,"text":"so you can get a sense of where they are; you see they're all over the world."},{"time":753000,"text":"The blue flags represent things that I've already photographed,"},{"time":756000,"text":"and the reds are places that I'm still trying to get to."},{"time":759000,"text":"You'll see also, there's a flag on Antarctica."},{"time":762000,"text":"I'm trying to travel there"},{"time":764000,"text":"to find 5,000 year-old moss,"},{"time":767000,"text":"which lives on the Antarctic Peninsula."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"So, I probably have about two more years left"},{"time":772000,"text":"on this project --"},{"time":774000,"text":"on this phase of the project,"},{"time":776000,"text":"but after five years,"},{"time":778000,"text":"I really feel like I know what's at the heart of this work."},{"time":781000,"text":"The oldest living things in the world"},{"time":783000,"text":"are a record and celebration of our past,"},{"time":786000,"text":"a call to action in the present"},{"time":789000,"text":"and a barometer of our future."},{"time":791000,"text":"They've survived for millennia"},{"time":793000,"text":"in desert, in the permafrost,"},{"time":795000,"text":"at the tops of mountains and at the bottom of the ocean."},{"time":798000,"text":"They've withstood"},{"time":800000,"text":"untold natural perils and human encroachments,"},{"time":803000,"text":"but now some of them are in jeopardy,"},{"time":805000,"text":"and they can't just get up and get out of the way."},{"time":808000,"text":"It's my hope that, by going to find these organisms,"},{"time":810000,"text":"that I can help draw attention"},{"time":812000,"text":"to their remarkable resilience"},{"time":814000,"text":"and help play a part in insuring"},{"time":816000,"text":"their continued longevity into the foreseeable future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}